    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Control) Germany/7–1145:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 411<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d411fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 19 of July 12 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 740.00119
                        Potsdam/7–1245).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 11, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6997. <hi rend="smallcaps">Comea</hi> 333. Soviet <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                        >EAC</gloss> delegation tonight communicated new formula for final <gloss
                        target="#t_para1">para</gloss> report transmitting agreement French zone in
                    Germany. This formula sent by Moscow following <persName corresp="#p_GFT1"
                        >Gusev</persName>’s return (<gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 6932,
                    July 10 <gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_MRE1"
                        >Murphy</persName> 30<note n="2" xml:id="d411fn2">
                        <ref target="#d410">Document No. 410</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p>[(]Sent to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_MRE1"
                        >Murphy</persName> as 34).</p>
                <p>Soviet formula follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The commission recommends that the question of determinating [<hi
                                rend="italic">sic</hi>] the boundaries of the French area in greater
                            Berlin, which area in consequence of the Soviet area of the city having
                            suffered the greatest destruction, will be formed out of the US and
                                <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> areas of greater Berlin, should be
                            referred for consideration to the Control Council in Berlin.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This formula has also been referred to <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> and
                    French Delegations. <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> meeting July 12, 4
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName>’s immediate personal comment to
                    acting Soviet representative<note n="3" xml:id="d411fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Georgy Filippovich Saksin</persName>.</note> was
                    that US formula<note n="4" xml:id="d411fn4">See the final sentence of the draft
                        report quoted in <ref target="#d407">document No. 407</ref>.</note> is more
                    practical since it does not attempt <pb facs="0734" n="602" xml:id="pg_602"/> in
                    absence of specific information and recommendations re division of Berlin to
                    decide in advance whether formation of French area will require adjustments in
                    two or three of present areas. <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName>
                    also made clear that US delegation not authorized to accept new Soviet
                    formula.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
